						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in front of the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla I (Jayasiṁha II)—A.D. 1027.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 9[50], Pra[bhava], Vaiśākha śu. [8], Monday,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1027, April 16,</hi> the weekday, however, being Sunday and not Monday. The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						<p>It registers a grant of land to the temple built by Bāchagāvuṇḍa, by Mahāsāmanta Daṇḍanātha <hi rend="bold">Rebbarasa.</hi> The gift land was situated in his <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> at <hi rend="bold">Gollagēri.</hi> </p>						

